@zachman_the_impera there's no more DS courses coming. So Mario Cirucit is the last DS course. But there's 2 more Wii courses, 1 more GBA, 3 more GCN, 1 more SNES, and 9 more Tour tracks. But most have gotten leaked, so avoid this if you don't want to know: Koopa Cape, Wii's Rainbow Road, Sunset Wilds, Los Angeles Laps, Vancouver Velocity, a Madrid course, and a Athens course. But those are datamined in Tour using assests, not proof.

@zachman_the_impera The leak isn't 100% correct by order, but at this point it's silly not to believe it. There's 4 more "New" courses but they're not new at all. These tracks are Tour tracks. Like Nintendo said Ninja Hideaway was a new track when the DLC launched, but it isn't; it released in Tour a year prior. Same with Sky-High Sundae, and Yoshi's Island. These were datamined in Tour way before it relased in 8 Deluxe. And files name in Tours files have the game/console it released on before the name. So like Waluigi Pinball it'd say "DSWP" so it's 'DS" And abbreviated Waluigi Pinball (WP). And the Yoshis Island course said "MobYI". Which "Mob" means mobile. And Tour is a mobile game. If it was a 8 Deluxe new course, it'd say like 8DYI. So they're not new, and Yoshi's Island just got annouced for Tour. As a Tour track. But yes, there are 4 "New" tracks left, one next wave, then 3 in the last. The evidence the leak isn't right is it got leaked in Wave 1 but no one fully believed him yet. But Wave 2, it got it exactly right in the order the datamine said. So he's right. But Wave 3 Waluigi Staduim was suppose to be in Wave 3,  but got swapped with Maple Treeway, but Maple Treeway was already leaked to come, but in Wave 6. And LA Laps was supposed to be in Wave 4, but wasn't. But besides a few minor order changes, it's still correct with what courses from which consoles will come. So, probably no more DS courses.
